<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910104-0010</DOCNO><DOCID>910104-0010.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- SCEcorp:   Mission Power Unit Renews   California Energy Lawsuit</HL><DATE>01/04/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   SCE CE</CO><IN>ELECTRIC UTILITIES (ELC)</IN><LP>   Mission Power Engineering Co. said it resumed legal actionagainst California Energy Co. and its partners aftersettlement talks failed to resolve a longstanding disputeinvolving construction work on eight power plants inCalifornia.   Mission Power, a unit of SCEcorp, a Rosemead, Calif.,holding company, said it suspended the lawsuit in Julypending the settlement discussions. However, &quot;the talksweren't going anywhere,&quot; a Mission Power spokesman saidyesterday.</LP><TEXT>   In the original complaint, filed last June in state courtin Inyo County, Mission Power claimed additional compensationof between $70 million and $80 million for its constructionwork on the plants. California Energy, San Francisco, hasdisputed the amounts claimed by Mission Power. The plantswere completed last year, Mission Power said.</TEXT></DOC>